Male
(
holotype
). BL 5.93, CL 2.95 (range 2.78–3.47), CW 2.22, CapW 1.09, EGW 0.83, LL 0.40, LW 0.40, SL 1.45, SW 1.24. Legs: 1423 (I: 11.82; II: 9.42; III: 8.40; IV: 10.98); ratio tibia I length:CW = 1:0.73. Male palp (
Fig. 6a,b
). RVTA stalk longer than in 

C. diehappy

; RDTA thick, curved and hook-like distally. Distal loop of sperm duct U-shaped with parallel limbs. Embolus a basally wide, curved rod with a subapical barb (
