). MA processes subequal, lateral process usually membraneous.

Female
(KS74066). BL 6.40, CL 2.95 (range 2.24–3.47), CW 1.85, CapW 1.35, EGW 0.90, LL 0.41, LW 0.43, SL 1.41, SW 1.23. Legs: 1423 (I: 9.89; II: 8.13; III: 7.16; IV: 9.25); ratio tibia I length:CW = 1:0.73. Epigynum (
Fig. 6c,d
). Median septum widest at middle. Paired fossae with relatively short lateral extensions (cf. 

C. diehappy

). Internal genitalia with very short copulatory ducts, about as wide as spermathecae.
